# My first Bard script!
Enter Romeo, a knave of 42.
Enter Juliet, a knave of 8.
Enter sum, a knave of Romeo plus Juliet.
Speak "The sum of Romeo and Juliet is:".
Speak sum.

Hark! shouldst sum is greater than 40, then :
    Speak "A grand sum indeed!".
Alas, else :
    Speak "A modest sum.".
Thus endeth the choice.
